</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="151" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="16" pageNumber="151">
<pageBreakToken pageId="16" pageNumber="151" start="start">Remarks</pageBreakToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="16" pageNumber="151">
Available barcode data were supplemented by a partial sequence of the holotype of 
<taxonomicName genus="L." lsidName="L. santista" pageId="16" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="santista">L. santista</taxonomicName>
, but were not, in our estimation, sufficient for unambiguous diagnosis or synonymy with 
<taxonomicName genus="L." lsidName="L. tacita" pageId="16" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="tacita">L. tacita</taxonomicName>
, particularly given that the primary types of 
<taxonomicName genus="L." lsidName="L. santista" pageId="16" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="santista">L. santista</taxonomicName>
are male, and that of 
<taxonomicName genus="L." lsidName="L. tacita" pageId="16" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="tacita">L. tacita</taxonomicName>
female.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
